article.description: Erica Williamson scored a career-high 21 points and Notre Dame (No. 4 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) held Georgetown to 32 percent shooting to beat the Hoyas 84-63 on Saturday night.
article.headline: No. 4 Notre Dame uses defense to stifle Georgetown
article.linkText: Williamson scores 21 to power No. 4 Irish
article.story:
SOUTH BEND, Ind. -- Erica Williamson scored a career-high 21 points and Notre Dame (No. 4 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) held Georgetown to 32 percent shooting to beat the Hoyas 84-63 on Saturday night.

Notre Dame (14-1, 3-0 Big East), which has won seven straight games, led by double digits for much of the first half. The Hoyas (11-4, 1-1) used a 15-9 run to close to 32-25 at halftime and cut the lead to 32-27 when Adria Crawford made a pair of free throws a minute into the second period.

Moments later, though, the Irish went on a 10-0 run to take a 48-31 lead when Kellie Watson made a 3-pointer. The Hoyas never got closer than 12 again.

Williamson, who also had a season-high 10 rebounds, finished with a career-high for points for a second straight game. She had 20 against DePaul on Tuesday.

Monica McNutt scored 16 and Morgan Williams added 14 for the Hoyas.
